# No AI Attribution In Git Artifacts

When creating git commits, commit messages, pull requests, or PR descriptions:

- Never mention Cursor, AI, Codex, ChatGPT, or any editor/assistant by name.
- Never add promotional text, editor branding, or tool-generated trailers.
- Never include links to Cursor, AI tools, transcripts, or internal agent artifacts.
- Keep commit messages and PR text focused only on the code change, user impact, and test plan.
- If any tool auto-inserts AI/editor attribution or links, remove them before finishing the commit or PR.

Examples to avoid:

- `Made with Cursor`
- `Generated by AI`
- `Co-authored-by: Cursor`
- PR descriptions containing Cursor/editor links or tool attribution
